item.title: Need help please ill make you co or admin on my server!
item.dc:creator: @Kizbits2000 Kizbits2000
item.description:
@Kizbits2000 wrote:

Basically if you are using a router you need to go into your router settings.
To do this go to your internet browser and try somthing on the lines of 192.168.2.1 or 192.168.0.1 or 192.168.1.1 all of those are normal for a router.

After you have done that Find somthing about either virtual servers or port fowarding.

When you have found this you need to enter the port that you need to foward ( the default port for most servers is 43594)
Set it to UDP and TCP (Incoming and Outgoing)

After this go to http://whatismyip.com/

And the IP that you see should be the ip thatr people should be able to connect to.

Hope this helps any problems with this just ask and i’ll be happy to help.

Kiz
